The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric stove and the hearth. Frame the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it down. Build a custom closet.
We always start with a quick pencil sketch...
The dirty step is finished.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried up :(
Ready for plastering next week
Happy with the small niche on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look at what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought about adding a lovely little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney sweep installed the cap and the rain cap. That should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. We install the floor tomorrow!
The rubber underlayment is laid, I improvised a wood shavings extractor using a roll of toilet paper as an accessory for the vacuum 😂
A portion of the boards has been sorted and is ready to be laid. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress has been slow today due to extremely delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on the knees! The cherry on top: the undrinkable instructions for assembling the new bed. We're going to sleep well tonight!
The floor of the hallway and all the baseboards remain to be done. The decorator comes in a month, so until then, at home, it's all about the elegance of plaster without any finishing touches.
Evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw or chisel where we want the floor to be perfectly fitted.
The rubber underlayment of the hallway is also laid
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then we left at 5 a.m. this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, had a nap, and completed the final stretch for the hallway; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing once the glue has dried.
